They both share a dependency due to nesting or the else statement.  A third option may be more maintainable depending on context.<p><pre><code>  if (a) {
    doSomething();
  }
  if ((a && b)||c) {
    doSomethingElse();
  }
</code></pre>
Granted, this is a case where refactoring is fairly trivial.<p>PS: The real question is does doSomethingElse depend on doSomething.
